<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900822-0048</DOCNO><DOCID>900822-0048.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Charter Medical Corp.:   SEC to Review Buy-Out   Led by Managers in 1988</HL><DATE>08/22/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10</SO><CO>   CMDA</CO><GV>SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION (SEC)</GV><LP>   Charter Medical Corp., Macon, Ga., said it was advised bythe Securities and Exchange Commission that the agency plansto review Charter's 1988 management-led leveraged buy-out.   No Charter executives have been interviewed by the SEC andno documents have been requested, according to J. RodneyLaughlin, an executive vice president of the psychiatric andgeneral hospital concern. &quot;It's so preliminary, I don't knowwhat they'll be reviewing,&quot; he said.</LP><TEXT>   SEC officials couldn't be reached.   In recent months, Charter has been struggling under $1.6billion in debt from the buy-out. The company has beencutting costs, by reducing personnel, among other measures.</TEXT></DOC>